President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate three individuals to key positions in his Administration. Howard R. Elliott of Indiana is nominated to be the Administrator of the Pipeline and Hazardous Materials Safety Administration at the Department of Transportation. Elliott has forty years of experience in the U.S. freight rail industry and has served as the group Vice President of Public Safety, Health, Environment and Security for CSX Transportation. He is recognized for his work in developing computer-based tools for emergency management officials and is a recipient of the Association of American Railroads prestigious Holden-Proefrock Award.

Paul Trombino III of Wisconsin is nominated to be the Administrator of the Federal Highway Administration at the Department of Transportation. Trombino is currently the President of McClure Engineering Company and previously served as the Director of the Iowa Department of Transportation. He has a background in civil engineering and economics.

William L. Wehrum of Delaware is nominated to serve as Assistant Administrator of the Environmental Protection Agency, Air and Radiation. Wehrum is a partner and the head of the Administrative Law Group at Hunton & Williams. He has experience in air quality issues, regulatory development, compliance counseling, and enforcement defense. Wehrum previously served as Acting Assistant Administrator for Air and Radiation at the U.S. Environmental Protection Agency.